        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2952311226" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer794987843677058048"><blockquote>If you want the math, it is calculated as the square root of the variance swap rate for a thirty-days term, quoted as an annualised variance. If you don&apos;t want the math, let&apos;s just say that what it does is show the implied volatility of the market for the coming month. It goes up and down minute by minute. The higher the index, the greater the uncertainty in the market, so traders call it &apos;the fear index.&apos; And it&apos;s liquid ifself, of course -there are VIX options and futures available to trade, a</blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText794987843677058048" style="display:none"><blockquote>If you want the math, it is calculated as the square root of the variance swap rate for a thirty-days term, quoted as an annualised variance. If you don't want the math, let's just say that what it does is show the implied volatility of the market for the coming month. It goes up and down minute by minute. The higher the index, the greater the uncertainty in the market, so traders call it 'the fear index.' And it's liquid ifself, of course -there are VIX options and futures available to trade, and we trade them.</blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="794987843677058048" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

